race.comment: TALLINGAS IMMORTAL (4) was nailed late fresh but went right on with the job last time at Albury when demolishing his rivals over 900m. Will burn across again from the wide alley and take plenty of reeling in. CHRISTMAS STAR (5) is busting to break through, denied by a lip last start at the Sapphire Coast. Strips rock-hard fit and gets the key booking of hot-hand hoop Boudvillain. Sure to be very competitive. MAGNA MAK (3) has returned in good order this campaign and gets an important 3kg claim. Goes well over this journey and is among the main hopes. DRAMA DODGER (9) returns and has trialled well in readiness. Goes well fresh and should be making her presence felt.
